AIG Falls to Lowest Since Last Year as Earnings Report Looms

-- B y   B r o o k e   S u t h e r l a n d
-- 
2011-08-04T19:28:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-04/aig-falls-to-lowest-since-last-year-as-earnings-report-looms.html
American International Group Inc. (AIG) ,
the bailed-out insurer, fell to the lowest in 17 months as
financial firms slumped.  AIG dropped $1.34, or 4.8 percent, to $26.85 at 3:24 p.m.
in  New York  Stock Exchange composite trading. The insurer has
plunged about 44 percent since Dec. 31. New York-based AIG is
scheduled to report second-quarter results today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brooke Sutherland in New York at 
 bsutherland5@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Kraut at   dkraut2@bloomberg.net 
